"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-29-paris-2024-olympic-nigerias-dtigress-makes-history-after-winning-first-game\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's D'Tigress made history after winning their first-ever game at the Paris 2024 Olympics by beating Australia on Monday morning.  D'Tigress finally won a game at the Olympics after beating Australia 75-62 in the opening game.  They were unfancied heading into the game but sprung a surprise result to kick-start their campaign.  Ezzine Kalu, who plies her trade in France, oozed class on the court, scoring 19 points.  Nigeria recovered from a slow start to win the first quarter 18-17.  They had an even better second quarter, winning 23-11.  D'Tigress will next play hosts France before wrapping up their group-stage campaign against Canada on August 4.  Paris 2024: D'Tigress stun Australia with first Olympic win 20 years  Scotland: Dessers tips Rangers to do big things next season  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  FIBA WWCQ: D'Tigress star Macaulay named in All-Star team  D'Tigress captain Ogoke retires from national team  FG fulfils pledge to D'Tigress for winning 2025 FIBA Women's Afrobasket  2026 FIBA World Cup Qualifiers: D'Tigress rally to 101-84 victory over Philippines  FIBA WWQ 2026: Gallant D'Tigress fall 77-60 to Korea  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"